      • sort

        public static void sort(java.util.List<Link> links)
        Given a List return them in a stable order. We don't define what that ordrer is, as long as it remains the smae from release to release. This is a kludge for the use of the mapped collection in 7.1. Because element indexes are no longer maintained order of the identity link list is not stable and needs to be sorted for unit tests that make XML comparisons to previously captured files.

        I'm starting with a focused approach since we're not going to have many s and not many of the unit tests appear to be impacted. If this becomes a chronic problem though we'll need to handle it in a more generic way in the XML serializer. Possibly have objects that need to be sorted implement a SortedList interface that BuiltinSerializers can use to determine whether to sort and how. Unfortunately that may require the regeneration of a large number of test files.

        That's a bit overkill for the moment so let's see if we can get away with calling it selectively for tests that care.

      • compareTo

        public int compareTo(Link other)
        Link order is determined by application combined with nativeIdentity. Technically we should include instance too, but I don't believe that is used by any of the unit tests.

        0=equal, -1=less, 1=greater

        Specified by:
        compareTo in interface java.lang.Comparable<Link>

      • equals

        public boolean equals(java.lang.Object o)
        Description copied from class: SailPointObject
        We override equals so that two objects will compare equal if they have the same database id or unique name, but are different Java objects. This is necessary for Hibernate because caches commonly have to be cleared or objects from one session need to be used to match things loaded in a different session.
        Overrides:
        equals in class SailPointObject
